# Circle App Kit configuration (Sprint 4 — Universal Token Swap)
#
# Circle App Kit's kit.swap()/kit.estimateSwap() require a "kit key" from
# the Circle Console to authenticate swap requests. Circle's own docs mark
# this as a credential ("do not log it, embed it in client-side source, or
# expose it in telemetry"). This project is a pure Vite/React frontend
# with no backend to proxy the call through, so this is a testnet-only
# tradeoff — the key still ends up in the client bundle. Rotate this key
# regularly and never use a mainnet/production kit key here. For a
# production deployment, proxy kit.swap()/kit.estimateSwap() through a
# backend so the key never ships to the browser.
#
# VITE_CIRCLE_KIT_KEY is the shared name — any future Circle App Kit
# feature in this app reads from it. VITE_SWAP_KIT_KEY is still read as a
# fallback so an existing deployment's .env keeps working unchanged; set
# one or the other, not both.
VITE_CIRCLE_KIT_KEY=

# Arc Testnet RPC providers (RpcManager — src/lib/rpc/)
#
# Four independent RPC endpoints, tried in this priority order via viem's
# fallback() transport with automatic latency-based failover. Every one
# is optional — any left unset falls back to the public default baked
# into src/lib/rpc/config.ts, so the app runs even with none of these set.
# Get a QuickNode/dRPC/Blockdaemon endpoint from their respective
# consoles for production use; the shared public endpoint
# (VITE_RPC_FALLBACK's default) is rate-limited and best used only as the
# last-resort tier it's configured as here.
VITE_RPC_PRIMARY=
VITE_RPC_SECONDARY=
VITE_RPC_THIRD=
VITE_RPC_FALLBACK=
